{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877552749,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ce972001W6tfXHiGLkdXmG","messageID":"msg_d7a8cdca2001DpmCutEDniC6dt","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD File Management API\n2: \n3: ## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the PicoD file management API that provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **File Upload/Download**: Transfer files between the host and sandbox environments with support for streaming large files\n19: 2. **Directory Listing**: Browse and query files within sandbox workspaces with filtering and pagination\n20: 3. **File Operations**: Create, delete, move, copy, and modify files and directories\n21: 4. **Path Security**: Enforce workspace boundaries and prevent path traversal attacks\n22: 5. **Quota Management**: Track and enforce storage limits per session\n23: \n24: This API serves as the file system interface between the agentcube platform and the sandbox orchestration system, enabling secure, quota-managed file operations with full audit logging.\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In Scope\n31: \n32: | Item | Detail |\n33: |------|--------|\n34: | **FileManager Interface** | Core file management interface with CRUD operations |\n35: | **Upload Operations** | Single file upload, multi-file upload, chunked upload for large files |\n36: | **Download Operations** | File download, directory archive download, streaming download |\n37: | **Directory Operations** | List, create, delete directories; recursive operations |\n38: | **File Metadata** | Size, permissions, modification time, MIME type detection |\n39: | **Path Validation** | Workspace-relative paths, path traversal prevention |\n40: | **Quota Tracking** | Storage usage monitoring and limit enforcement |\n41: | **File Watching** | Optional file system change notifications |\n42: | **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for file operation failures |\n43: | **Integration Points** | Integration with status store for operation tracking |\n44: \n45: ### Out of Scope\n46: \n47: - Changes to the sandbox orchestration interface (AR-009)\n48: - Modifications to storage implementations (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n49: - HTTP server implementation (separate PicoD daemon)\n50: - JWT authentication layer\n51: - Command execution APIs (AR-015)\n52: - Real-time collaborative editing\n53: - Version control integration (Git operations)\n54: - File content search/indexing\n55: - Encryption at rest (handled at storage layer)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Design\n60: \n61: ### File Structure\n62: \n63: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n64: |------|------|--------------|\n65: | `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | FileManager implementation | ~300 |\n66: | `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | File operation type definitions | ~120 |\n67: | `pkg/picod/upload.go` | Upload handling and chunking | ~150 |\n68: | `pkg/picod/download.go` | Download handling and streaming | ~150 |\n69: | `pkg/picod/path.go` | Path validation and security | ~100 |\n70: | `pkg/picod/quota.go` | Quota management and tracking | ~80 |\n71: | `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | File-specific error definitions | ~60 |\n72: | `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | Unit tests | ~250 |\n73: \n74: ### Architecture\n75: \n76: ```\n77: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n78: │                    Client Application                    │\n79: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n80:                       │\n81:                       ▼\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │              PicoD FileManager API                       │\n84: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n85: │  Upload()   │  Download()    │  List()                │\n86: │  Delete()   │  Move()        │  Copy()                │\n87: │  Mkdir()    │  GetMetadata() │  Watch()               │\n88: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n89: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n90: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n91: │              Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                 │\n92: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Core Types\n96: \n97: #### FileManager Interface\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: type FileManager interface {\n101:     // Upload operations\n102:     Upload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n103:     UploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n104:     \n105:     // Download operations\n106:     Download(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n107:     StreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n108:     \n109:     // File operations\n110:     Delete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n111:     Move(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n112:     Copy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n113:     \n114:     // Directory operations\n115:     List(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n116:     Mkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n117:     Rmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n118:     \n119:     // Metadata operations\n120:     GetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n121:     SetPermissions(ctx context.Context, req PermissionsRequest) error\n122:     \n123:     // Quota operations\n124:     GetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n125:     \n126:     // Watching\n127:     Watch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n128: }\n129: ```\n130: \n131: #### UploadRequest / UploadResult\n132: \n133: ```go\n134: type UploadRequest struct {\n135:     SessionID       string\n136:     SourcePath      string      // Path on host\n137:     DestinationPath string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n138:     Overwrite       bool\n139:     ContentType     string\n140:     \n141:     // For chunked uploads\n142:     ChunkSize       int64       // 0 for auto-detect\n143:     TotalSize       int64       // Known size, 0 if unknown\n144: }\n145: \n146: type UploadResult struct {\n147:     FileID          string\n148:     Path            string\n149:     Size            int64\n150:     Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n151:     UploadedAt      time.Time\n152: }\n153: \n154: type UploadChunkRequest struct {\n155:     UploadID        string\n156:     ChunkIndex      int\n157:     ChunkData       io.Reader\n158:     ChunkSize       int64\n159:     IsLast          bool\n160: }\n161: \n162: type UploadChunkResult struct {\n163:     ChunkIndex      int\n164:     ReceivedBytes   int64\n165:     UploadComplete  bool\n166: }\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### DownloadRequest / DownloadResult\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: type DownloadRequest struct {\n173:     SessionID       string\n174:     Path            string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n175:     Recursive       bool        // For directories\n176:     ArchiveFormat   string      // \"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\" for recursive download\n177: }\n178: \n179: type DownloadResult struct {\n180:     FileID          string\n181:     Path            string\n182:     Size            int64\n183:     ContentType     string\n184:     Data            io.ReadCloser\n185:     Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: #### ListRequest / ListResult\n190: \n191: ```go\n192: type ListRequest struct {\n193:     SessionID       string\n194:     Path            string\n195:     Recursive       bool\n196:     Pattern         string      // Glob pattern for filtering\n197:     IncludeHidden   bool\n198:     Pagination      *Pagination\n199: }\n200: \n201: type Pagination struct {\n202:     Limit   int\n203:     Offset  int\n204:     Cursor  string\n205: }\n206: \n207: type ListResult struct {\n208:     Entries         []FileInfo\n209:     TotalCount      int\n210:     NextCursor      string\n211: }\n212: \n213: type FileInfo struct {\n214:     Name            string\n215:     Path            string\n216:     Type            FileType      // file, directory, symlink\n217:     Size            int64\n218:     Permissions     os.FileMode\n219:     CreatedAt       time.Time\n220:     ModifiedAt      time.Time\n221:     Checksum        string        // For files\n222:     MimeType        string\n223: }\n224: \n225: type FileType string\n226: \n227: const (\n228:     FileTypeFile      FileType = \"file\"\n229:     FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n230:     FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n231: )\n232: ```\n233: \n234: #### DeleteRequest / MoveRequest / CopyRequest\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: type DeleteRequest struct {\n238:     SessionID       string\n239:     Path            string\n240:     Recursive       bool        // For directories\n241: }\n242: \n243: type MoveRequest struct {\n244:     SessionID       string\n245:     SourcePath      string\n246:     DestinationPath string\n247:     Overwrite       bool\n248: }\n249: \n250: type CopyRequest struct {\n251:     SessionID       string\n252:     SourcePath      string\n253:     DestinationPath string\n254:     Overwrite       bool\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: #### QuotaInfo\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: type QuotaInfo struct {\n262:     SessionID       string\n263:     UsedBytes       int64\n264:     TotalBytes      int64           // 0 for unlimited\n265:     AvailableBytes  int64\n266:     FileCount       int64\n267:     MaxFileCount    int64           // 0 for unlimited\n268: }\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Execution Flows\n274: \n275: ### File Upload (Small Files)\n276: \n277: ```\n278: Upload(ctx, req)\n279:     │\n280:     ▼\n281: Validate request parameters\n282:     │\n283:     ▼\n284: Resolve and validate destination path\n285:     │\n286:     ▼\n287: Check quota availability\n288:     │\n289:     ├─ Insufficient → Return ErrQuotaExceeded\n290:     │\n291:     ▼\n292: Upload file to sandbox\n293:     │\n294:     ▼\n295: Verify checksum\n296:     │\n297:     ▼\n298: Update quota tracking\n299:     │\n300:     ▼\n301: Return UploadResult\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ### File Upload (Large Files - Chunked)\n305: \n306: ```\n307: Upload(ctx, req) - Initialize\n308:     │\n309:     ▼\n310: Validate request parameters\n311:     │\n312:     ▼\n313: Create upload session\n314:     │\n315:     ▼\n316: Return UploadID\n317: \n318: UploadChunk(ctx, chunkReq) - Repeat for each chunk\n319:     │\n320:     ▼\n321: Validate upload session\n322:     │\n323:     ▼\n324: Receive chunk data\n325:     │\n326:     ▼\n327: Store chunk temporarily\n328:     │\n329:     ▼\n330: Update upload progress\n331:     │\n332:     ▼\n333: If IsLast:\n334:     │\n335:     ▼\n336: Assemble chunks\n337:     │\n338:     ▼\n339: Verify checksum\n340:     │\n341:     ▼\n342: Move to final destination\n343:     │\n344:     ▼\n345: Update quota tracking\n346:     │\n347:     ▼\n348: Return UploadChunkResult\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ### File Download\n352: \n353: ```\n354: Download(ctx, req)\n355:     │\n356:     ▼\n357: Validate request parameters\n358:     │\n359:     ▼\n360: Resolve and validate source path\n361:     │\n362:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n363:     │\n364:     ▼\n365: Check if path is directory and recursive flag\n366:     │\n367:     ├─ Directory + !Recursive → Return ErrIsDirectory\n368:     ├─ Directory + Recursive → Create archive stream\n369:     └─ File → Create file stream\n370:     │\n371:     ▼\n372: Stream data to client\n373:     │\n374:     ▼\n375: Return DownloadResult with ReadCloser\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Directory Listing\n379: \n380: ```\n381: List(ctx, req)\n382:     │\n383:     ▼\n384: Validate request parameters\n385:     │\n386:     ▼\n387: Resolve and validate path\n388:     │\n389:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n390:     │\n391:     ▼\n392: Query directory contents\n393:     │\n394:     ├─ !Recursive → List immediate children\n395:     └─ Recursive → Walk directory tree\n396:     │\n397:     ▼\n398: Apply pattern filter if specified\n399:     │\n400:     ▼\n401: Apply pagination\n402:     │\n403:     ▼\n404: Return ListResult\n405: ```\n406: \n407: ### File Deletion\n408: \n409: ```\n410: Delete(ctx, req)\n411:     │\n412:     ▼\n413: Validate request parameters\n414:     │\n415:     ▼\n416: Resolve and validate path\n417:     │\n418:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n419:     │\n420:     ▼\n421: Check if directory and recursive flag\n422:     │\n423:     ├─ Directory + !Recursive → Return ErrDirectoryNotEmpty\n424:     │\n425:     ▼\n426: Delete file/directory\n427:     │\n428:     ▼\n429: Update quota tracking\n430:     │\n431:     ▼\n432: Return nil\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ---\n436: \n437: ## Error Handling\n438: \n439: ### Error Types\n440: \n441: | Error | Code | Description |\n442: |-------|------|-------------|\n443: | `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed file operation request |\n444: | `ErrFileNotFound` | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | Specified path does not exist |\n445: | `ErrPathNotAllowed` | `PATH_NOT_ALLOWED` | Path outside workspace boundaries |\n446: | `ErrPathTraversal` | `PATH_TRAVERSAL` | Detected path traversal attempt |\n447: | `ErrPermissionDenied` | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | Insufficient permissions for operation |\n448: | `ErrQuotaExceeded` | `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | Storage quota limit reached |\n449: | `ErrFileExists` | `FILE_EXISTS` | File already exists (without overwrite) |\n450: | `ErrIsDirectory` | `IS_DIRECTORY` | Expected file but got directory |\n451: | `ErrNotDirectory` | `NOT_DIRECTORY` | Expected directory but got file |\n452: | `ErrDirectoryNotEmpty` | `DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY` | Cannot delete non-empty directory |\n453: | `ErrTransferFailed` | `TRANSFER_FAILED` | Upload/download operation failed |\n454: | `ErrChecksumMismatch` | `CHECKSUM_MISMATCH` | Data integrity check failed |\n455: | `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox environment not available |\n456: \n457: ### FileError Structure\n458: \n459: ```go\n460: type FileError struct {\n461:     Code       string\n462:     Message    string\n463:     Path       string\n464:     Details    map[string]interface{}\n465: }\n466: \n467: func (e *FileError) Error() string {\n468:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (path=%s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Path)\n469: }\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Path Security\n475: \n476: ### Path Validation Rules\n477: \n478: ```go\n479: type PathValidator struct {\n480:     WorkspaceRoot string\n481: }\n482: \n483: func (v *PathValidator) Validate(path string) (string, error) {\n484:     // 1. Clean the path\n485:     cleaned := filepath.Clean(path)\n486:     \n487:     // 2. Check for absolute paths\n488:     if filepath.IsAbs(cleaned) {\n489:         return \"\", ErrPathNotAllowed\n490:     }\n491:     \n492:     // 3. Resolve symlinks and check boundaries\n493:     fullPath := filepath.Join(v.WorkspaceRoot, cleaned)\n494:     resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPath)\n495:     if err != nil {\n496:         return \"\", err\n497:     }\n498:     \n499:     // 4. Ensure resolved path is within workspace\n500:     if !strings.HasPrefix(resolved, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n501:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     // 5. Check for traversal patterns in original path\n505:     if strings.Contains(path, \"..\") {\n506:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n507:     }\n508:     \n509:     return resolved, nil\n510: }\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ### Security Measures\n514: \n515: 1. **Workspace Isolation**: All paths are resolved relative to a sandbox-specific workspace root\n516: 2. **Symlink Resolution**: Symlinks are resolved and validated before operations\n517: 3. **Path Traversal Detection**: `../` patterns and absolute paths are rejected\n518: 4. **Permission Checks**: File permissions are validated before read/write operations\n519: 5. **Quota Enforcement**: Storage limits are checked before write operations\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Impact Analysis\n524: \n525: ### Files Created\n526: \n527: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n528: |------|--------------|-------------|\n529: | `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | ~300 | Core FileManager implementation |\n530: | `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | ~120 | Type definitions for file operations |\n531: | `pkg/picod/upload.go` | ~150 | Upload handling and chunking logic |\n532: | `pkg/picod/download.go` | ~150 | Download handling and streaming |\n533: | `pkg/picod/path.go` | ~100 | Path validation and security |\n534: | `pkg/picod/quota.go` | ~80 | Quota management and tracking |\n535: | `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | ~60 | File-specific error definitions |\n536: | `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | ~250 | Unit tests |\n537: \n538: ### Dependencies\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: import (\n542:     \"context\"\n543:     \"crypto/sha256\"\n544:     \"errors\"\n545:     \"fmt\"\n546:     \"io\"\n547:     \"os\"\n548:     \"path/filepath\"\n549:     \"strings\"\n550:     \"time\"\n551:     \n552:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox\"\n553:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n554: )\n555: ```\n556: \n557: | Package | Purpose |\n558: |---------|---------|\n559: | `pkg/sandbox` | Sandbox interface for file operations (AR-009) |\n560: | `pkg/store` | Status persistence for operation tracking (AR-012/13/14) |\n561: \n562: ### Downstream Consumers\n563: \n564: | Consumer | Usage |\n565: |----------|-------|\n566: | Session Manager | File operations within user sessions |\n567: | CLI Tooling | `kubectl-agentcube cp` commands |\n568: | HTTP API Layer | REST endpoints for file management |\n569: | IDE Integration | File sync for remote development |\n570: \n571: ### Performance Characteristics\n572: \n573: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n574: |-----------|------------|-------|\n575: | Upload (small) | O(n) | n = file size |\n576: | Upload (chunked) | O(n) | n = total file size |\n577: | Download | O(n) | n = file size |\n578: | List (non-recursive) | O(m) | m = directory entries |\n579: | List (recursive) | O(m) | m = total entries |\n580: | Delete | O(1) | Per file/directory |\n581: | Move/Copy | O(n) | n = file size |\n582: | Quota Check | O(1) | Cached value lookup |\n583: \n584: ---\n585: \n586: ## Alternatives Considered\n587: \n588: ### Alternative 1: Direct Sandbox File Access Without API Layer\n589: \n590: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n591: |--------|------------|\n592: | **Pros** | Simpler architecture; fewer abstraction layers; potentially better performance |\n593: | **Cons** | No centralized quota management; scattered permission checks; harder to implement unified audit logging; no support for chunked uploads |\n594: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — API layer provides necessary abstraction for quota management, security enforcement, and operation tracking |\n595: \n596: ### Alternative 2: Use Standard SFTP Protocol\n597: \n598: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n599: |--------|------------|\n600: | **Pros** | Industry standard; existing client libraries; familiar to users |\n601: | **Cons** | Additional protocol complexity; requires SFTP server in sandbox; harder to integrate with Kubernetes patterns; quota management requires custom extensions |\n602: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom API better fits the agentcube architecture and provides more control over quota and security |\n603: \n604: ### Alternative 3: Leverage containerd/cri-o File Operations\n605: \n606: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n607: |--------|------------|\n608: | **Pros** | Native integration with container runtime; potentially more efficient |\n609: | **Cons** | Runtime-specific; limited to runtime capabilities; harder to implement features like chunked upload |\n610: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Higher-level API provides better abstraction and portability across different sandbox implementations |\n611: \n612: ### Alternative 4: Event-Driven File Operations\n613: \n614: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n615: |--------|------------|\n616: | **Pros** | Better decoupling; natural fit for async operations; good for file watching |\n617: | **Cons** | Higher complexity; harder to implement synchronous operations like download; more moving parts |\n618: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Direct method calls provide better control, simpler error handling, and are sufficient for the current use case |\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ## Risks and Mitigations\n623: \n624: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n625: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n626: | Path traversal vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Strict path validation; workspace boundary enforcement; symlink resolution |\n627: | Quota bypass via sparse files | Low | Medium | Accurate size calculation; check both apparent and actual size |\n628: | Memory exhaustion from large uploads | Low | High | Streaming upload with chunked transfer; configurable chunk sizes |\n629: | Concurrent modification conflicts | Medium | Medium | Optimistic locking; ETag/checksum validation; atomic operations |\n630: | Storage exhaustion from failed uploads | Low | Medium | Automatic cleanup of incomplete uploads; upload session timeouts |\n631: | Denial of service via many small files | Medium | Medium | File count quotas; rate limiting on file creation |\n632: | Sandbox integration failures | Medium | High | Graceful error handling; fallback to error status; retry logic |\n633: \n634: ---\n635: \n636: ## Verification\n637: \n638: ### Unit Tests\n639: \n640: ```bash\n641: # Run all picod file manager tests\n642: make test PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n643: \n644: # Run with race detector\n645: go test -race ./pkg/picod/...\n646: \n647: # Run specific test categories\n648: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestUpload\"\n649: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestDownload\"\n650: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestPathValidation\"\n651: ```\n652: \n653: ### Integration Tests\n654: \n655: ```bash\n656: # Run integration tests (requires sandbox)\n657: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -tags=integration\n658: \n659: # With coverage\n660: go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n661: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n662: ```\n663: \n664: ### Manual Verification\n665: \n666: ```bash\n667: # Build verification\n668: go build ./pkg/picod/...\n669: \n670: # Interface compliance check\n671: go build ./...\n672: \n673: # Lint check\n674: make lint PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n675: ```\n676: \n677: ### Test Scenarios\n678: \n679: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n680: |----------|-----------------|\n681: | Upload small file | Returns UploadResult with correct checksum |\n682: | Upload large file (chunked) | All chunks received, assembled correctly |\n683: | Upload to existing path (no overwrite) | Returns ErrFileExists |\n684: | Download file | Returns correct data with matching checksum |\n685: | Download directory (recursive) | Returns archive with all contents |\n686: | List directory | Returns all entries with correct metadata |\n687: | List with pattern filter | Returns only matching entries |\n688: | Delete file | File removed, quota updated |\n689: | Delete non-empty directory (no recursive) | Returns ErrDirectoryNotEmpty |\n690: | Path traversal attempt | Returns ErrPathTraversal |\n691: | Quota exceeded on upload | Returns ErrQuotaExceeded |\n692: | Invalid UTF-8 filename | Returns ErrInvalidRequest |\n693: | Concurrent uploads to same path | One succeeds, others fail with ErrFileExists |\n694: \n695: ---\n696: \n697: ## References\n698: \n699: - [PicoD Design](changes/AR-016/design.md) — Detailed design document\n700: - [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n701: - [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-016/tests.md) — Test specifications\n702: - [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Related command execution API\n703: - [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n704: - [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n705: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n706: \n707: ---\n708: \n709: ## Success Criteria\n710: \n711: 1. ✅ FileManager interface fully implemented\n712: 2. ✅ Upload operations support both single-file and chunked modes\n713: 3. ✅ Download operations support streaming and archive creation\n714: 4. ✅ Directory listing with filtering and pagination\n715: 5. ✅ Complete file operations (delete, move, copy)\n716: 6. ✅ Path validation prevents traversal attacks\n717: 7. ✅ Quota tracking and enforcement\n718: 8. ✅ File watching support\n719: 9. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n720: 10. ✅ Integration tests passing\n721: 11. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n722: \n723: ---\n724: \n725: *AR-016 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 725 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API\n\n## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the PicoD file management API that provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **File Upload/Download**: Transfer files between the host and sandbox environments with support for streaming large files\n2. **Directory Listing**: Browse and query files within sandbox workspaces with filtering and pagination\n3. **File Operations**: Create, delete, move, copy, and modify files and directories","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877552729,"end":1775877552747}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877552764,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ceeb2001TBtZl1LAIC6Pju","messageID":"msg_d7a8cdca2001DpmCutEDniC6dt","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n16: │                           │                              │\n17: │                           ▼                              │\n18: │                   Token Validation                       │\n19: │                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Middleware Flow\n24: \n25: ```\n26: Incoming Request\n27:        │\n28:        ▼\n29: ┌──────────────┐\n30: │ Extract      │\n31: │ Bearer Token │\n32: └──────────────┘\n33:        │\n34:        ▼\n35: ┌──────────────┐\n36: │ Validate     │\n37: │ Token Format │\n38: └──────────────┘\n39:        │\n40:        ▼\n41: ┌──────────────┐\n42: │ Verify       │\n43: │ Signature    │\n44: └──────────────┘\n45:        │\n46:        ▼\n47: ┌──────────────┐\n48: │ Validate     │\n49: │ Claims       │\n50: │ (exp, iss)   │\n51: └──────────────┘\n52:        │\n53:        ▼\n54:    [Valid] ────► Call Handler\n55:        │\n56:    [Invalid] ──► Return 401/403\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ## Key Interfaces\n60: \n61: ### JWTValidator\n62: \n63: Core interface for token validation.\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type JWTValidator interface {\n67:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n68:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Middleware Function\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: // Middleware wraps an HTTP handler with JWT validation\n76: func JWTMiddleware(validator JWTValidator, opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Claims Structure\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: type Claims struct {\n83:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n84:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n85:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n86:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Validation Options\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type ValidationOptions struct {\n94:     Issuer        string        // Expected issuer claim\n95:     ClockSkew     time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for exp validation\n96:     AllowedAlgs   []string      // Allowed signing algorithms\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ## Supported Algorithms\n101: \n102: | Algorithm | Type | Key Format |\n103: |-----------|------|------------|\n104: | HS256 | HMAC-SHA256 | []byte (symmetric) |\n105: | RS256 | RSA-SHA256 | *rsa.PublicKey |\n106: \n107: ## Configuration\n108: \n109: ### Environment Variables\n110: \n111: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n112: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n113: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 only | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n114: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 only | - | Path to RSA public key file |\n115: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n116: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | 1m | Clock skew tolerance |\n117: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | RS256 | Signing algorithm |\n118: \n119: ## Error Handling\n120: \n121: ### Error Types\n122: \n123: - `ErrMissingToken`: No Authorization header present\n124: - `ErrInvalidTokenFormat`: Malformed Authorization header\n125: - `ErrInvalidSignature`: Signature verification failed\n126: - `ErrTokenExpired`: Token has expired\n127: - `ErrInvalidIssuer`: Issuer claim mismatch\n128: - `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`: Algorithm not in allowed list\n129: \n130: ### HTTP Responses\n131: \n132: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n133: |----------|--------|------|\n134: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n135: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n136: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n137: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n138: \n139: ## Security Considerations\n140: \n141: - Tokens must be transmitted via HTTPS\n142: - HMAC secrets must be securely stored\n143: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n144: - Short token expiration recommended\n145: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal\n146: \n147: ## Performance Considerations\n148: \n149: - RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n150: - Consider caching parsed keys\n151: - Minimize allocations in hot path\n152: - Early rejection for missing headers\n153: \n154: ## Open Questions\n155: \n156: 1. Should we support JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) for key rotation?\n157: 2. Do we need audience claim validation?\n158: 3. Should we support multiple issuers?\n159: 4. Is token binding to specific endpoints required?\n\n(End of file - total 159 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n│                           │                              │\n│                           ▼                              │\n│                   Token Validation                       │\n│                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775877552733,"end":1775877552762}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877552767,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8cf493001eo1dQXc3jZgOx9","messageID":"msg_d7a8cdca2001DpmCutEDniC6dt","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n10: \n11: The PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valid HS256 token passes validation\n22: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with HS256 and secret \"test-secret\"\n23: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"HS256\", Secret: []byte(\"test-secret\")}`\n24: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the HMAC signature\n26: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Valid RS256 token passes validation\n29: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with RS256 using a private key\n30: - **AND** the corresponding public key is configured\n31: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"RS256\", PublicKey: rsaPubKey}`\n32: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the RSA signature\n34: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns error\n37: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with invalid signature\n38: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidSignature`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Expired token returns error\n42: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `exp` claim in the past\n43: - **AND** no clock skew configured\n44: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n45: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrTokenExpired`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Clock skew allows near-expired tokens\n48: - **GIVEN** a JWT token expired 30 seconds ago\n49: - **AND** `ClockSkew: 1m` configured\n50: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL accept the token\n52: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Wrong issuer returns error\n55: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `iss: \"other-service\"`\n56: - **AND** `ExpectedIssuer: \"auth-service\"` configured\n57: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n58: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidIssuer`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Unsupported algorithm returns error\n61: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with ES256\n62: - **AND** `AllowedAlgorithms: [\"HS256\", \"RS256\"]` configured\n63: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n64: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: HTTP Middleware\n69: \n70: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that extracts and validates JWT tokens from requests.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Request with valid token proceeds to handler\n73: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <valid_token>`\n74: - **AND** JWTMiddleware is configured with valid validator\n75: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n76: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL extract the token\n77: - **AND** validate it successfully\n78: - **AND** call the wrapped handler\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Request without token returns 401\n81: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request without Authorization header\n82: - **WHEN** the request is processed by JWTMiddleware\n83: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n84: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Request with invalid token format returns 401\n87: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: invalid_format`\n88: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n89: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n90: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n93: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <bad_sig_token>`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n96: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n99: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with expired JWT token\n100: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n101: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n102: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Invalid issuer returns 403\n105: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with token from wrong issuer\n106: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n107: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 403\n108: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}`\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Claims are added to request context\n111: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with claims\n112: - **AND** a request with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n113: - **WHEN** the wrapped handler is called\n114: - **THEN** the request context SHALL contain the parsed `Claims`\n115: - **AND** the handler can retrieve claims via `GetClaims(ctx)`\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: Configuration\n120: \n121: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: HS256 configuration loads secret from env\n124: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_SECRET=my-secret`\n125: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=HS256`\n126: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n127: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use HMAC with secret \"my-secret\"\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: RS256 configuration loads public key from file\n130: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=/path/to/key.pem`\n131: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=RS256`\n132: - **AND** a valid RSA public key file at that path\n133: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n134: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use the loaded RSA public key\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Issuer is required configuration\n137: - **GIVEN** no `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` environment variable\n138: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n139: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error\n140: - **AND** fail fast on startup\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Clock skew configuration is parsed\n143: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW=2m`\n144: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n145: - **THEN** the validator SHALL allow 2 minutes of clock skew\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Changes to Base Specification\n150: \n151: This AR adds authentication middleware to AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API). No modifications to existing interfaces.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## New Interfaces\n156: \n157: ### JWTValidator Interface\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: package jwt\n161: \n162: import \"context\"\n163: \n164: // JWTValidator validates JWT tokens\n165: type JWTValidator interface {\n166:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n167: }\n168: \n169: // Claims represents validated JWT claims\n170: type Claims struct {\n171:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n172:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n173:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n174:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n175: }\n176: \n177: // ValidationOptions configures the validator\n178: type ValidationOptions struct {\n179:     Algorithm       string\n180:     Secret          []byte        // For HS256\n181:     PublicKey       *rsa.PublicKey // For RS256\n182:     ExpectedIssuer  string\n183:     ClockSkew       time.Duration\n184:     AllowedAlgs     []string\n185: }\n186: \n187: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with options\n188: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Middleware Function\n192: \n193: ```go\n194: // MiddlewareOptions configures the middleware behavior\n195: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n196:     Validator    JWTValidator\n197:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n198: }\n199: \n200: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\n201: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n202: \n203: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from context\n204: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ### Error Types\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: var (\n211:     ErrMissingToken         = errors.New(\"jwt: missing bearer token\")\n212:     ErrInvalidTokenFormat   = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid token format\")\n213:     ErrInvalidSignature     = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid signature\")\n214:     ErrTokenExpired         = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n215:     ErrInvalidIssuer        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid issuer\")\n216:     ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm = errors.New(\"jwt: unsupported algorithm\")\n217: )\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ---\n221: \n222: ## Modified Interfaces\n223: \n224: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Behavioral Changes\n229: \n230: | Behavior | Before | After |\n231: |----------|--------|-------|\n232: | API authentication | None | JWT token validation required |\n233: | Request processing | Direct | Through middleware layer |\n234: | Error responses | Application-defined | Standardized auth errors |\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Dependencies\n239: \n240: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n241: |------------|---------|---------|\n242: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT parsing and validation |\n243: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Local | Integration with AR-015 |\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## File Index\n248: \n249: | Path | Purpose |\n250: |------|---------|\n251: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options types |\n252: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation |\n253: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware |\n254: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Configuration loading |\n255: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n256: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests |\n257: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Middleware tests |\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Constants\n262: \n263: | Constant | Value | Description |\n264: |----------|-------|-------------|\n265: | `defaultClockSkew` | `1m` | Default clock skew tolerance |\n266: | `authorizationHeader` | `\"Authorization\"` | HTTP header name |\n267: | `bearerPrefix` | `\"Bearer \"` | Token prefix |\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## Configuration\n272: \n273: ### Environment Variables\n274: \n275: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n276: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n277: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n278: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 | - | Path to RSA public key PEM file |\n279: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n280: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | `1m` | Clock skew tolerance |\n281: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | `RS256` | Signing algorithm |\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## API Endpoints Summary\n286: \n287: This AR provides middleware functionality; no new endpoints are exposed.\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Migration Notes\n292: \n293: - Add `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` dependency to go.mod\n294: - Configure JWT environment variables before deployment\n295: - Apply middleware to protected routes using `JWTMiddleware(opts)`\n296: - Existing unauthenticated endpoints remain unaffected\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n301: \n302: 1. **Token Validation**: HS256 and RS256 tokens validated correctly\n303: 2. **Claims Validation**: exp, iss claims validated with clock skew support\n304: 3. **Middleware**: HTTP middleware extracts and validates bearer tokens\n305: 4. **Error Responses**: Appropriate HTTP 401/403 responses for auth failures\n306: 5. **Configuration**: All settings configurable via environment variables\n307: 6. **Context Integration**: Parsed claims available via GetClaims(ctx)\n308: 7. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on validation logic\n309: 8. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end middleware flow tested\n\n(End of file - total 309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877552735,"end":1775877552764}}}}
