{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877566929,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8d211a001PC0G01imnja4t6","messageID":"msg_d7a8cfab2001Jz0sD0gOmgET94","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Test Categories\n4: \n5: ### Unit Tests\n6: \n7: #### validator_test.go\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: // TestValidateToken_HS256_Success - Valid HS256 token\n11: // TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong HMAC secret\n12: // TestValidateToken_RS256_Success - Valid RS256 token\n13: // TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong RSA key\n14: // TestValidateToken_Expired - Expired token\n15: // TestValidateToken_NotYetValid - Token used before iat\n16: // TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer - Issuer mismatch\n17: // TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm - Algorithm not allowed\n18: // TestValidateToken_Malformed - Invalid JWT format\n19: // TestValidateToken_MissingClaims - Required claims missing\n20: ```\n21: \n22: #### middleware_test.go\n23: \n24: ```go\n25: // TestMiddleware_ValidToken - Request with valid token passes\n26: // TestMiddleware_MissingToken - Request without token returns 401\n27: // TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat - Malformed Authorization header\n28: // TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken - Expired token returns 401\n29: // TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer - Wrong issuer returns 403\n30: // TestMiddleware_ValidationError - Other validation errors\n31: // TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation - Claims added to context\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Integration Tests\n35: \n36: ```go\n37: // TestIntegration_EndToEnd - Full middleware flow\n38: // TestIntegration_RealToken - Test with actual JWT library\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Test Data\n42: \n43: #### Sample HS256 Token\n44: \n45: ```go\n46: // Secret: \"test-secret-12345\"\n47: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user123\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <future>}\n48: ```\n49: \n50: #### Sample RS256 Token\n51: \n52: ```go\n53: // Generated with test RSA key pair\n54: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user456\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <future>}\n55: ```\n56: \n57: #### Expired Token\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user789\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <past>}\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ## Coverage Targets\n64: \n65: - Line coverage: >= 85%\n66: - Branch coverage: >= 80%\n67: - Critical paths: 100%\n68: \n69: ## Test Environment\n70: \n71: - Go 1.21+\n72: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` for test token generation\n73: - Mock HTTP handlers for middleware testing\n74: \n75: ## Test Execution\n76: \n77: ```bash\n78: # Unit tests only\n79: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -short\n80: \n81: # All tests including integration\n82: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n83: \n84: # With coverage\n85: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n86: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n87: ```\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Test Specification\n\n## Test Categories\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### validator_test.go\n\n```go\n// TestValidateToken_HS256_Success - Valid HS256 token\n// TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong HMAC secret\n// TestValidateToken_RS256_Success - Valid RS256 token\n// TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong RSA key\n// TestValidateToken_Expired - Expired token\n// TestValidateToken_NotYetValid - Token used before iat\n// TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer - Issuer mismatch\n// TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm - Algorithm not allowed\n// TestValidateToken_Malformed - Invalid JWT format\n// TestValidateToken_MissingClaims - Required claims missing\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md","time":{"start":1775877566912,"end":1775877566928}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877566931,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8d28c8001Oz2GF7TcUaIvus","messageID":"msg_d7a8cfab2001Jz0sD0gOmgET94","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD JWT authentication middleware.\n6: \n7: ## Phase 1: Core Types and Interfaces\n8: \n9: - [ ] Define JWTValidator interface\n10: - [ ] Define Claims struct with standard JWT claims\n11: - [ ] Define ValidationOptions struct\n12: - [ ] Define MiddlewareOptions struct\n13: - [ ] Define error types for validation failures\n14: \n15: ## Phase 2: Token Validation\n16: \n17: - [ ] Implement HS256 signature verification\n18: - [ ] Implement RS256 signature verification\n19: - [ ] Implement token parsing and claims extraction\n20: - [ ] Implement expiration validation with clock skew\n21: - [ ] Implement issuer claim validation\n22: - [ ] Implement algorithm validation\n23: \n24: ## Phase 3: HTTP Middleware\n25: \n26: - [ ] Implement JWTMiddleware function\n27: - [ ] Implement bearer token extraction from Authorization header\n28: - [ ] Implement error handling and HTTP response generation\n29: - [ ] Support configurable middleware options\n30: \n31: ## Phase 4: Configuration\n32: \n33: - [ ] Implement configuration from environment variables\n34: - [ ] Support HMAC secret loading\n35: - [ ] Support RSA public key loading from file\n36: - [ ] Validate configuration on startup\n37: \n38: ## Phase 5: Integration\n39: \n40: - [ ] Create middleware factory for PicoD API\n41: - [ ] Document integration points with AR-015\n42: - [ ] Provide examples of applying middleware to routes\n43: \n44: ## Phase 6: Testing\n45: \n46: - [ ] Write unit tests for token validation\n47: - [ ] Write unit tests for middleware\n48: - [ ] Write integration tests\n49: - [ ] Test with real JWT tokens\n50: \n51: ## Estimated Timeline\n52: \n53: - Phase 1: 0.5 day\n54: - Phase 2: 0.75 day\n55: - Phase 3: 0.5 day\n56: - Phase 4: 0.25 day\n57: - Phase 5: 0.25 day\n58: - Phase 6: 0.5 day\n59: \n60: Total: 2-2.5 days\n61: \n62: ## Dependencies\n63: \n64: - AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API (for integration)\n65: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` or similar JWT library\n66: \n67: ## File Deliverables\n68: \n69: | Path | Purpose |\n70: |------|---------|\n71: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options types |\n72: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation |\n73: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware |\n74: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Configuration loading |\n75: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n76: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests |\n77: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Middleware tests |\n\n(End of file - total 77 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD JWT authentication middleware.\n\n## Phase 1: Core Types and Interfaces\n\n- [ ] Define JWTValidator interface\n- [ ] Define Claims struct with standard JWT claims\n- [ ] Define ValidationOptions struct\n- [ ] Define MiddlewareOptions struct\n- [ ] Define error types for validation failures\n\n## Phase 2: Token Validation\n\n- [ ] Implement HS256 signature verification\n- [ ] Implement RS256 signature verification\n- [ ] Implement token parsing and claims extraction\n- [ ] Implement expiration validation with clock skew","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md","time":{"start":1775877566915,"end":1775877566930}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877566934,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8d2d8c0015cy2F8RrY74Jgp","messageID":"msg_d7a8cfab2001Jz0sD0gOmgET94","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n16: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n17: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Key Interfaces\n24: \n25: #### CommandExecutor\n26: \n27: The primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n28: \n29: ```go\n30: type CommandExecutor interface {\n31:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n32:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n33:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n34:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n35:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: #### ExecutionRequest\n40: \n41: Configuration for a command execution.\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n45:     Command     string\n46:     Args        []string\n47:     WorkingDir  string\n48:     Environment map[string]string\n49:     Timeout     time.Duration\n50:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n51:     SessionID   string\n52: }\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### ExecutionResult\n56: \n57: Result of a command execution.\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: type ExecutionResult struct {\n61:     ID         ExecutionID\n62:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n63:     ExitCode   int\n64:     Stdout     []byte\n65:     Stderr     []byte\n66:     StartedAt  time.Time\n67:     FinishedAt time.Time\n68:     Error      *ExecutionError\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: ### Synchronous Execution\n75: \n76: ```\n77: 1. Client calls Execute()\n78: 2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n79: 3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n80: 4. Command is executed with monitoring\n81: 5. Output is captured\n82: 6. Result is returned to client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Asynchronous Execution\n86: \n87: ```\n88: 1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n89: 2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n90: 3. Background worker picks up execution\n91: 4. Status updates to \"running\"\n92: 5. Output is streamed to buffer\n93: 6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n94: 7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Error Handling\n98: \n99: ### Error Types\n100: \n101: - `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n102: - `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n103: - `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n104: - `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n105: - `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n106: - `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n107: \n108: ### Status States\n109: \n110: ```\n111: pending → running → completed\n112:               ↓\n113:             failed\n114:               ↓\n115:            cancelled\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Security Considerations\n119: \n120: - Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n121: - Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n122: - No direct shell access\n123: - Environment variable filtering\n124: - Working directory restrictions\n125: \n126: ## Performance Considerations\n127: \n128: - Connection pooling to sandbox service\n129: - Output buffering with size limits\n130: - Concurrent execution limits\n131: - Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n132: \n133: ## Open Questions\n134: \n135: 1. Maximum output size limits?\n136: 2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n137: 3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n138: 4. Execution queue prioritization?\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775877566918,"end":1775877566932}}}}
