{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877729913,"sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8d5ce6001ue8icoR5wNd1SN","messageID":"msg_d7a8d320a001NR1gulI5nd5ATw","sessionID":"ses_28573627cffeWYVrNGFwRUqE0j","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod/jwt` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer that provides secure token-based authentication for agentcube platform endpoints. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Token Validation**: Support for HS256 (HMAC-SHA256) and RS256 (RSA-SHA256) JWT signature verification\n2. **Claims Validation**: Verification of standard claims including expiration (`exp`), issuer (`iss`), and issued-at (`iat`) with configurable clock skew tolerance\n3. **HTTP Middleware**: Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers that extracts and validates Bearer tokens from Authorization headers\n4. **Configuration Management**: Environment-based configuration for JWT secrets, public keys, issuer validation, and algorithm selection\n5. **Context Integration**: Propagation of parsed claims through request context for downstream handlers\n6. **Standardized Error Responses**: Consistent HTTP 401/403 responses for authentication and authorization failures\n\nThis middleware integrates with the PicoD command execution API (AR-015) to provide a secure authentication layer, ensuring only valid, trusted requests are processed by the agentcube platform.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **JWTValidator Interface** | Core interface for token validation with multiple algorithms |\n| **HS256 Support** | HMAC-SHA256 signature verification using shared secrets |\n| **RS256 Support** | RSA-SHA256 signature verification using public keys |\n| **Token Parsing** | JWT token parsing with header and claims extraction |\n| **Claims Validation** | Standard claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with clock skew |\n| **HTTP Middleware** | Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers |\n| **Bearer Token Extraction** | Authorization header parsing with Bearer scheme |\n| **Context Propagation** | Claims injection into request context |\n| **Configuration Loading** | Environment variable-based configuration |\n| **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for validation failures |\n| **HTTP Responses** | Standardized JSON error responses (401/403) |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Token generation/issuance (handled by external identity provider)\n- Refresh token mechanism\n- OAuth2/OIDC integration\n- Session management\n- Rate limiting (separate middleware)\n- Audit logging (handled by separate layer)\n- JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) support (future enhancement)\n- Audience claim validation (future enhancement)\n- Multiple issuer support (future enhancement)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options type definitions | ~80 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation | ~150 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware implementation | ~120 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Environment-based configuration | ~80 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error type definitions | ~60 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests for validator | ~200 |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Unit tests for middleware | ~150 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Client Application                    │\n│         (with JWT token from Identity Provider)          │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    HTTP Server                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │           JWTMiddleware                          │    │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────┐  │    │\n│  │  │   Extract   │──►│  Validate   │──►│ Verify  │  │    │\n│  │  │    Token    │  │   Format    │  │Signature│  │    │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └────┬────┘  │    │\n│  │                                         │       │    │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐      │       │    │\n│  │  │   Inject    │◄──│  Validate   │◄─────┘       │    │\n│  │  │   Claims    │  │   Claims    │              │    │\n│  │  │  to Context │  │ (exp, iss)  │              │    │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                          │                              │\n│                          ▼                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │              PicoD API Handler                   │    │\n│  │           (AR-015 Command Execution)             │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Middleware Flow\n\n```\nIncoming Request\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Extract      │\n│ Bearer Token │\n│ from Header  │\n└──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├─ Missing ──► Return 401\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Validate     │\n│ Token Format │\n└──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Verify       │\n│ Signature    │\n│ (HS256/RS256)│\n└──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Validate     │\n│ Claims       │\n│ (exp, iss)   │\n└──────────────┘\n       │\n       ├─ Expired ──► Return 401\n       ├─ Bad Issuer ► Return 403\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Call Handler │\n│ with Claims  │\n│ in Context   │\n└──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### JWTValidator Interface\n\n```go\ntype JWTValidator interface {\n    // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n    ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### Claims Structure\n\n```go\ntype Claims struct {\n    Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`  // User/subject identifier\n    Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`  // Token issuer\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n    IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`  // Issued-at timestamp\n}\n```\n\n#### ValidationOptions\n\n```go\ntype ValidationOptions struct {\n    Algorithm      string           // \"HS256\" or \"RS256\"\n    Secret         []byte           // HMAC secret for HS256\n    PublicKey      *rsa.PublicKey   // RSA public key for RS256\n    ExpectedIssuer string           // Expected issuer claim\n    ClockSkew      time.Duration    // Allowed clock skew (default 1m)\n    AllowedAlgs    []string         // Allowed algorithms whitelist\n}\n```\n\n#### MiddlewareOptions\n\n```go\ntype MiddlewareOptions struct {\n    Validator    JWTValidator\n    ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### NewValidator Constructor\n\n```go\n// NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with the specified options\nfunc NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n```\n\n#### Middleware Function\n\n```go\n// JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\nfunc JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n\n// GetClaims retrieves validated claims from request context\nfunc GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Flows\n\n### Token Validation (HS256)\n\n```\nValidateToken(token)\n    │\n    ▼\nParse JWT header to extract algorithm\n    │\n    ▼\nVerify algorithm is in AllowedAlgs\n    │\n    ├─ Unsupported ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n    │\n    ▼\nVerify algorithm matches configured Algorithm\n    │\n    ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n    │\n    ▼\nParse JWT claims\n    │\n    ├─ Malformed ──► Return ErrInvalidTokenFormat\n    │\n    ▼\nVerify HMAC signature using configured Secret\n    │\n    ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n    │\n    ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n    │\n    ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn parsed Claims\n```\n\n### Token Validation (RS256)\n\n```\nValidateToken(token)\n    │\n    ▼\nParse JWT header to extract algorithm\n    │\n    ▼\nVerify algorithm is RSA-based and allowed\n    │\n    ▼\nParse JWT claims\n    │\n    ▼\nVerify RSA signature using configured PublicKey\n    │\n    ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n    │\n    ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n    │\n    ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn parsed Claims\n```\n\n### HTTP Middleware Processing\n\n```\nJWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n    │\n    ▼\nIncoming HTTP request\n    │\n    ▼\nExtract Authorization header\n    │\n    ├─ Missing ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n    │\n    ▼\nCheck Bearer prefix\n    │\n    ├─ Missing/Invalid ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n    │\n    ▼\nExtract token string\n    │\n    ▼\nCall validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    │\n    ├─ ErrInvalidSignature ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n    ├─ ErrTokenExpired ──────► Return 401 + JSON error\n    ├─ ErrInvalidIssuer ─────► Return 403 + JSON error\n    ├─ Other errors ─────────► Return 401 + JSON error\n    │\n    ▼\nAdd claims to request context\n    │\n    ▼\nCall wrapped handler with enhanced context\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Code | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `ErrMissingToken` | `MISSING_TOKEN` | No Authorization header present |\n| `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | `INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT` | Malformed Authorization header or JWT |\n| `ErrInvalidSignature` | `INVALID_SIGNATURE` | Signature verification failed |\n| `ErrTokenExpired` | `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Token has expired |\n| `ErrInvalidIssuer` | `INVALID_ISSUER` | Issuer claim mismatch |\n| `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | `UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM` | Algorithm not in allowed list |\n\n### HTTP Responses\n\n| Scenario | Status | Body |\n|----------|--------|------|\n| Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}` |\n| Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n| Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n| Unsupported algorithm | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"unsupported algorithm\"}` |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Token Transmission\n- Tokens MUST be transmitted via HTTPS in production\n- HTTP in development only with appropriate warnings\n\n### Key Management\n- HMAC secrets MUST be securely stored (e.g., Kubernetes secrets)\n- RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n- Private keys for token signing are NOT handled by this middleware\n\n### Validation Security\n- Short token expiration recommended (minutes to hours)\n- Clock skew tolerance kept minimal (default 1 minute)\n- Algorithm explicitly specified to prevent \"none\" algorithm attacks\n- Allowed algorithms whitelist prevents unexpected algorithm usage\n\n### Path Security\n- Workspace isolation ensures tokens are scoped appropriately\n- Claims context propagation follows request lifecycle\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | ~80 | Claims and options type definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | ~150 | JWTValidator implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | ~120 | HTTP middleware implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | ~80 | Environment-based configuration |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | ~60 | Error type definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | ~200 | Unit tests for validator |\n| `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | ~150 | Unit tests for middleware |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"crypto/rsa\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"net/http\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation library |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| PicoD API Server | Protects command execution endpoints (AR-015) |\n| Session Manager | Validates tokens for session operations |\n| CLI Tooling | Token-aware request handling |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Token parsing | O(1) | Fixed JWT structure parsing |\n| HS256 validation | O(1) | Fast HMAC computation |\n| RS256 validation | O(1) | Slower RSA signature verification |\n| Context propagation | O(1) | Simple pointer passing |\n\n### Algorithm Performance Comparison\n\n| Algorithm | Relative Speed | Use Case |\n|-----------|----------------|----------|\n| HS256 | Fast (1x) | Internal services, symmetric trust |\n| RS256 | Slower (~10x) | External clients, asymmetric trust |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Standard OAuth2/OIDC Middleware\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Full standard compliance; broader ecosystem support; automatic token refresh handling |\n| **Cons** | Heavy dependency footprint; more complex configuration; unnecessary features for our use case |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom JWT middleware provides sufficient functionality with minimal dependencies |\n\n### Alternative 2: Implement Custom JWT Parsing (No Library)\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Zero external dependencies; full control over implementation; minimal binary size |\n| **Cons** | Security risk if implementation flawed; maintenance burden; lacks battle-tested validation |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Using established `golang-jwt/jwt` library provides security and reliability |\n\n### Alternative 3: API Gateway-Level Authentication\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Centralized authentication; service doesn't handle auth logic; works with existing gateways |\n| **Cons** | Requires gateway deployment; less flexible per-endpoint configuration; claims not available to service |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — In-middleware approach provides better integration with PicoD context and per-handler flexibility |\n\n### Alternative 4: Session-Based Authentication (Cookies)\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Stateless clients; simpler for browser-based clients; built-in session management |\n| **Cons** | Requires session storage; CSRF concerns; less suitable for API-only clients |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — JWT tokens better fit the stateless API architecture and cross-service authentication needs |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Weak HMAC secrets | Low | Critical | Configuration validation; minimum secret length enforcement; secure secret generation guidance |\n| RSA key confusion attacks | Low | High | Explicit algorithm configuration; algorithm whitelist; reject \"none\" algorithm |\n| Clock skew causing token rejection | Medium | Medium | Configurable clock skew tolerance; clear documentation on time synchronization |\n| Token replay attacks | Low | Medium | Short token expiration; consider token binding in future |\n| Algorithm confusion attacks | Low | Critical | Strict algorithm validation; separate code paths for HS256/RS256 |\n| Key extraction from memory | Low | High | Use secure string handling; minimize key exposure time |\n| JWT library vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Use well-maintained library; regular dependency updates; CVE monitoring |\n| Configuration errors on startup | Medium | High | Fail-fast validation; clear error messages; configuration documentation |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all JWT middleware tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestValidateToken\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestMiddleware\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run integration tests\nmake integration-test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# Interface compliance check\ngo build ./...\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Valid HS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n| Valid RS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n| Invalid HS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n| Invalid RS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n| Expired token | Returns ErrTokenExpired |\n| Token with clock skew within tolerance | Returns parsed Claims |\n| Wrong issuer | Returns ErrInvalidIssuer |\n| Unsupported algorithm | Returns ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm |\n| Request with valid token (middleware) | Proceeds to handler with claims in context |\n| Request without token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n| Request with invalid format (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n| Request with expired token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n| Request with wrong issuer (middleware) | Returns 403 with JSON error |\n| Configuration loading from environment | Correctly parses all settings |\n| Missing required configuration | Returns error on startup |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD JWT Design](changes/AR-017/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [PicoD JWT Delta Spec](changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n- [PicoD JWT Tests](changes/AR-017/tests.md) — Test specifications\n- [PicoD JWT Plan](changes/AR-017/plan.md) — Implementation plan\n- [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Base API that this middleware protects\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns for agentcube\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ JWTValidator interface fully implemented with HS256 and RS256 support\n2. ✅ Token validation correctly verifies signatures for both algorithms\n3. ✅ Claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with configurable clock skew\n4. ✅ HTTP middleware extracts and validates Bearer tokens\n5. ✅ Context propagation allows handlers to access parsed claims\n6. ✅ Environment-based configuration with validation\n7. ✅ Standardized HTTP 401/403 error responses\n8. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n9. ✅ Integration tests passing\n10. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n11. ✅ Documentation complete with usage examples\n\n---\n\n*AR-017 — Module: pkg/picod/jwt — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877729794,"end":1775877729910}}}}
